Ok, This Location is a most. Love the New York Style Pizza.

I will give Este Pizzeria a strong 9.1 this was an experience that I will love to enjoy every Friday night, The theme at the restaurant totally felt like a Pizza shop.

Parking was a bit limited but did not have a problem to get in and out.

If You find that orange color on the Cheese you will get a good NYC Style Pizza and as you can see we got orange!!!

Ann Thanks for the interaction and a great welcome You and Your Team as well as your Young Son give this place what many are missing in the SLC valley, Super awesome to have met you guys, and I will see you guys soon.

I had the Cheese 18 inch and a pepperoni 18 inch as well I can tell you I loved it.

Great pie! Very large slices and delicious! I ate way too many slices, and didn‚Äôt regret a single bite!

Staff was very friendly and helpful, very clean restaurant with some older TV‚Äôs and old school rock alternative music posters on the wall.

Really cool wall art and decent decor.

I 100% will return for a slice when visiting SLC

The pizza was great, the place was really cool with all of the art and had a different vibe to it. The person taking the order didn't seem too happy to be there and appeared frustrated with us as we tried to figure out what to order. It was also pretty expensive for two of their smallest pizzas, a salad, and a side for 60 dollars is a bit. Google search showed here as a place for fire roasted pizza, but I don't think that was correct. I would probably take friends here for the vibe and artwork.

detailedReviews.text: This a great place for groups or a quick bite alone. The prices are reasonable. The service is fast and friendly. Unpretentious. Real. I will be back with my son. I recommend that you try. Give them a visit. You won‚Äôt be disappointed.

detailedReviews.author: Robert G (Bobby)
detailedReviews.text:
I enjoy pizza, but this place is way above average. It's NOT "Just Another Pizza." The wood fired pizza was a light and crispy crust that was fluffy and soft inside.

The crust had a traditionally slightly salty flavor, but just the right hint of sweetness to it. It was a slice above. Lol get it slice above, pizza, haha.

The sauce. Great flavor, with balanced seasoning. No one seasoning over powered the other. Great fresh tomato flavor, with just the right size of tomato chunks in it.

Toppings...
We'll we did a half and half.
One side was a combo and the other was Lasagna.

I went for lasagna first and it was amazing.
I was feeling like combo is sometimes a bunch of under or over cooked veggies and, well not really my thing. How about WOW! I have never had a combo I felt it was to die for! Ok that might be a little extreme, but man oh man, it was delicious. The veggies were well balanced and cooked just right. Fresh? Yes, very!

Both sides had sausage. It wasn't the typical sausage, it was sliced fresh Italian sausage. We'll done Este Pizza.

Atmosphere -
Real cool vibe in this place. You can see the cool decals all over the partition and graffiti walls. Real cool art, and I'm not a graffiti buff. Open ceilings. Great music! Cool rock and roll 70's - Today. Heard some Stones, Halen, Sublime...

We came at an odd hour (pretty early for pizza). Really brunch for the 4 of us, they were just getting going.

As always, that was my/our experience! I can't implore you enough to give it a shot and post your own review!

detailedReviews.text: I really like all the stickers on the booths. It's entertaining to look at. The garlic knots are my favorite! Soooo yummy! I have come to Estes for a very long time and it never gets old. I really love their pizza and it's a cool chill vibe!

detailedReviews.author: David Melville
detailedReviews.text: A Real pizzaria, delicious, Real pizza, Thank you

detailedReviews.author: A'Lissa Olson
detailedReviews.text:
It was a cold and windy afternoon‚Ä¶ and pizza sounded like the antidote. Where to as we made our way south? Este Pizza of course!

This wasn‚Äôt my first, nor will it be my last visit to this casual Sugarhouse eatery. Is it the 90‚Äôs rock music, the tacky stickers all over the booths, or the broken candy machine at the exit that keep me coming back? No, it‚Äôs the orzo salad! :) Not that the pizzas are bad. Our veggie lasagna pizza was fantastic. Fresh ingredients, chewy but not too thick crust, and just the right amount of everything made it a new go-to. The small is not small at all and provides 8 large slices. We couldn‚Äôt finish it, but will enjoy the leftovers.

This is an order at the counter and they bring it to you kind of place. But, the woman who greeted us, took our order, brought out our food, and provided our to-go box was pleasant, helpful and kind. She deserves a raise and helps temper the skater/snowboarder indifferent vibe.

But, back to the orzo salad with its bed of spinach, warm and flavorful orzo filled with toasted pine nuts, and the fresh ricotta cheese. It is the best thing on the menu! I literally dream about this salad. I think it may have shrunk in size (or my desire for more has increased). It‚Äôs enough to share with a friend, but you may wish to didn‚Äôt have to. I do have to say that it is best eating in, so that the orzo is still warm. Mmmm. I want more now!

detailedReviews.text: I've been coming here for many years and the pizza is the best New York Style pizza there is in Utah. Every pizza comes out hot and fresh and tastes amazing. As well as their garlic knots are to die for. I hope they never close
